<subSubSection id="40A71A405F23E6E6A93D42329408946B" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="F3A42126BBB7AD38C4C35E3FF4A072C3" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="641D24C2EC11ACE6E8A3B7AB0211EC13" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
This species is often collected with 
<taxonomicName id="5CF06605A6A9978074B639575F835C99" genus="L." lsidName="L. phragmitidis" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="phragmitidis">
<emphasis id="C705F43701533F76072DC4E7E8A038F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">L. phragmitidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Schrank, 1781) and 
<taxonomicName id="51C9105428ABAC0A6157A8DB39F24DAE" genus="L." lsidName="L. stigma" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="stigma">
<emphasis id="06DBC9F162170B1EE6C4466D20CD44B8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">L. stigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Meigen, 1818), and it is a dominant species in Hemu (China: Xinjiang, Burqin). These species often aggregate in shaded understory plants in white birch forests during the day (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C7D93382122F2C8FED6BC8CABCCD72FF" captionStart="Figures 45–47" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figures 45 - 47. Limonia sylvicola, male 45 male habitus, lateral view 46 head and thorax, dorsal view 47 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures45-47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456146" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">46</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
